title: 2019 Ukrainian presidential election - Wikipedia
snippet: The Central Election Commission (CEC) announced that Zelenskyy won the second round with 73.22% of the total vote (or 74.96% of the valid vote). The elections were recognized as free and fair by the Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe. Poroshenko became the third incumbent Ukrainian president to directly lose reelection, after Viktor Yushchenko in 2010 and Leonid Kravchuk in 1994 (only Leonid Kuchma has ever won reelection, in 1999).

title: Volodymyr Zelenskyy - Wikipedia
snippet: After months of ambiguous statements, on 31 December, less than four months from the election, Zelenskyy announced his candidacy for president of Ukraine on the New Year's Eve evening show on the TV channel 1+1. His announcement up-staged the New Year's Eve address of incumbent president Petro Poroshenko on the same channel, which Zelenskyy said was unintentional and attributed to a technical glitch.

title: r/ukraine on Reddit: People should never forget that Poroshenko was equally as great of a president as Zelensky
snippet: Poroshenko's government was instrumental in many important reforms, yes, but he also tried to sit on two chairs at once, with little action against oligarchs and corruption.
